---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import { QUESTION_RULES } from "@/lib/rules";
import { RulesQuiz } from "@/components/RulesQuiz";
---

<Layout className="bg-main text-white p-8">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8 mt-12">
    <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold font-poppins">Rules & Tips</h1>
      <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '')}/`} class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">Back to Map</a>
    </div>
    <p class="text-slate-400 mt-2 italic">Be sure to read to the end for a fun rules check quiz!</p>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold border-b border-slate-700 pb-2">1. Game Overview</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-slate-300"><strong>Hide & Seek</strong> is a continuous game of cat-and-mouse played across a designated local transit system. One player (the <strong>Hider</strong>) uses public transit to travel to a secret location and establish a Hiding Zone (more on this below). The remaining players (the <strong>Seekers</strong>) work cooperatively to track down the Hider by asking strategic questions.</p>
      <p class="text-slate-300">The game operates in rounds. Once the Seekers can visually see the Hider, the round ends, and a new player becomes the Hider. The player who remains hidden for the longest total time wins the game.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold border-b border-slate-700 pb-2">2. Setting Up the Game</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-300">
        <li><strong>The Map:</strong> The game map is strictly defined by the \"Calgary Rapid Transit Network\". All gameplay and movement must occur within the bounds of this network.</li>
        <li><strong>The Head Start:</strong> Before the Seekers can begin their pursuit, the Hider is granted a designated head start period (e.g., 45 to 60 minutes, depending on the agreed-upon game size).</li>
        <li><strong>Transit Only:</strong> During the head start, the Hider may only travel using approved public transit (trains, buses) and walking. No private vehicles or ride-shares are allowed.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold border-b border-slate-700 pb-2">3. The Hiding Zone & The Hiding Spot</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-slate-300">Once the head start concludes, the Hider must permanently lock in their final Hiding Zone.</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-300">
        <li><strong>The Anchor Station:</strong> The Hider must choose a valid transit station to act as the anchor for their location.</li>
        <li><strong>Zone Radius:</strong> The Hider must remain within a specific radius of their Anchor Station for the remainder of the round.</li>
        <li><strong>Stationary Rule:</strong> Once the Hiding Zone is locked in, the Hider cannot leave this radius until they are caught. They may move freely within the zone until the end game begins.</li>
        <li><strong>Visuallizing the Hiding Zones:</strong> Use the right sidebar (pin icon) to toggle on/off the visuals for the Hiding Zones.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mt-6 mb-3 text-slate-200">The End Game & Your Hiding Spot</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-300">
        Once the seekers have entered your hiding zone the end game has begun. You must stay put in a single spot until they've found you, this is your final hiding spot.
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-300">
        Hiding spots can be anywhere within your hiding zone, but they must be somewhere that is <strong>publicly accessible during all game hours</strong>. You cannot, for example, hide in a bathroom stall or someone's house. You should also make sure that staying in your spot for an extended period of time will not raise any suspicions or create the potential for you to get kicked out, for this reason avoid stores or other businesses, even if they are open during all game hours.
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-300">
        Your hiding spot must also be within 3 meters of a marked path or road on Google Maps. Viable paths and roads should be easy to discern, but if there's any question as to whether one counts, the test is whether or not Google Maps will use them for walking directions.
      </p>
      <p class="text-slate-300">
        If you aren't where you want to be when the seekers enter your hiding zone, too bad! Wherever you're standing at that moment is your hiding spot. (If, for whatever reason, you aren't somewhere publicly accessible when the end game starts, you must immediately go to the nearest possible publicly accessible spot and stay there instead.)
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold border-b border-slate-700 pb-2">4. The Seeking Phase & Questions</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-slate-300">To locate the Hider, Seekers use the webapp to ask specific types of questions. The Hider must answer truthfully.</p>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-medium mb-3 mt-6 text-slate-200">Question Categories</h3>
      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
        {Object.entries(QUESTION_RULES).map(([key, rule]) => (
          <div class="bg-slate-800 p-4 rounded-xl border border-slate-700">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold capitalize text-blue-400 mb-2">{key === "radius" ? "Radar" : key}</h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300">{rule}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p class="mb-4 text-slate-300"><strong>No Street View:</strong> Seekers must physically go to places to search for the Hider's photos. However, you may use Satellite View.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold border-b border-slate-700 pb-2">5. Time Penalties</h2>
      <p class="mb-4 text-slate-300">To balance the flow of information, the game utilizes a <strong>Time Penalty</strong> system.</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-300">
        <li><strong>Cost of Information:</strong> Every time the Seekers ask a question to narrow down the Hider's location, a Time Penalty is incurred.</li>
        <li><strong>How it Works:</strong> This penalty compensates the Hider for revealing clues about their location. Each question type carries a specific time cost that is applied to the game clock.</li>
        <li><strong>Current Penalties:</strong> Match: 15m, Radar: 10m, Closest: 20m, Hot/Cold: 10m, Photo: 5m, Measure: 15m.</li>
        <li><strong>Strategic Seeking:</strong> Because asking questions carries a time cost, Seekers must work together to ask the most efficient and strategic questions possible.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="italic mt-4 text-sm text-slate-400">(Note: The webapp automatically calculates, tracks, and applies all Time Penalties as questions are logged).</p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold border-b border-slate-700 pb-2">6. Ending the Round</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-300">
        <li><strong>The Catch:</strong> Seekers must physically locate the Hider. Once a Seeker spots the Hider (or gets within a predetermined visual tagging distance), the round immediately ends.</li>
        <li><strong>Logging the Time:</strong> The webapp calculates the total time the Hider survived, factoring in their baseline hidden time plus any accumulated Time Penalties from the Seekers' questions.</li>
        <li><strong>Next Round:</strong> The players reset, a new Hider is chosen, and the next head start begins.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold border-b border-slate-700 pb-2">7. Tips for a Better Game</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-slate-300">
        <li><strong>Poor Cellular Reception?</strong> The game works offline as much as possible. If you expect poor internet access in certain areas, open the Options drawer and click <em>"Cache All Possible Places"</em> while you have a connection. This will download all map data needed for the game in advance.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold border-b border-slate-700 pb-2">8. Rules Check: The Quiz!</h2>
      <RulesQuiz client:load />
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
